cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modeling and analysis of a cache-enabled heterogeneous network.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper introduces a maximum received power strategy for deducing novel algorithms of the success probability and area spectral efficiency.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper considers caching multimedia contents in the HetNet.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of the HetNet.
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security issues related to caching and communication in the HetNet.
